# Auto-resolve the version-line conflict every concurrent PR collides on.
#
# spyc bumps `version = "x.y.z"` on every PR, so any two in-flight branches
# conflict on that one line. The `spyc-semver` merge driver (src/merge_driver.rs;
# spyc installs it into the repo's git config on launch) runs a three-way merge
# and keeps the higher semver for a version-only conflict — anything else still
# surfaces as a real conflict.
Cargo.toml merge=spyc-semver
# Cargo.lock keeps "our" side on conflict; the next `cargo build` / `cargo update
# -p spyc` regenerates the spyc version entry deterministically (no network).
# This never produces a spurious lock conflict — the proven rebase recipe.
Cargo.lock merge=ours
